Installation of jenkins using bash on ec2 instance



	1. Vim jenkins.sh

	2. Paste the script below 

#!/bin/bash

echo "Installing Jenkins repository..."
sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo \
https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo

echo "Importing Jenkins key..."
sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key

echo "Upgrading packages..."
sudo dnf upgrade -y

echo "Installing Jenkins..."
sudo dnf install jenkins -y

echo "Starting Jenkins service..."
sudo systemctl start jenkins

echo "Enabling Jenkins to start on boot..."
sudo systemctl enable jenkins

echo "Checking Jenkins status..."
sudo systemctl status jenkins --no-pager

echo "Opening port 8080 in firewall..."
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=8080/tcp
sudo firewall-cmd --reload

echo "Jenkins installation completed."
echo "Access Jenkins at: http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:8080"

echo "Initial admin password:"
sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword



	3. :wq to save 

	4. To complete installation


Sh jenkins.sh 
